<p><strong>Devourer's Scepter</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Great Hammers" href="/Great+Hammers">Great Hammer (Warhammer)</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Devourer's Scepter</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a>. It is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a>&nbsp;for high strength players who can hold this weapon's weight. The weight is worth the ability to crush&nbsp;enemy armor, sometimes along with the enemy itself.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Scepter in the shape of a serpent devouring the world. This<br>weapon will one day become the very symbol of the Lord of&nbsp;<br>Blasphemy.<br>One of the legendary armaments.</em></p> 
 <p><em>A vision of the future briefly seen by Rykard in his final moments<br>before being devoured by the great serpent.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Devourer's Scepter in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Devourer's Scepter weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Knight Bernahl" href="/Knight+Bernahl" target="">Knight/Recusant Bernahl</a>&nbsp;when defeated. You will find him at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Warmaster's Shack" href="/Warmaster's+Shack" target="">Warmaster's Shack</a> [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1216&amp;lat=-179.7&amp;lng=101.5&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1216&amp;lat=-179.7&amp;lng=101.5&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>] or in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Crumbling Farum Azula" href="/Crumbling+Farum+Azula" target="">Crumbling Farum Azula</a> when he invades you [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4507&amp;lat=-121&amp;lng=219.02522&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4507&amp;lat=-121&amp;lng=219.02522&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>].&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/SM11swgGzw0?t=4240">Video Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Devourer's Scepter Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Devourer of Worlds" href="/Devourer+of+Worlds" target="">Devourer of Worlds</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Devourer's Scepter</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1000.</li> 
 <li>One of the longest Warhammers in the game and great for pyromancer builds, especially since the 1-handed moveset is fantastic for rollcatching. The Ash of War isn't great but is capable of catching people off guard if they get too close. Ideal to&nbsp;be used in Strength/Faith builds.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Devourer's Scepter</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Devourer's Scepter Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Devourer's Scepter Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
