				<li id="16717771" class="cmnt-root" data="-2" data-d="1655523008000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578984/Devourer's-Scepter" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">17 Jun 2022 23:30</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16717771" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">An interesting weapon.<br/><br/>Can hit pretty hard. With 99 in Str + Dex + Fth it has AR of 983 1h and 1015 2h.<br/><br/>WA with these stats basic pleb Soldiers near Gatefront grace for 472. It does however, deal Fire damage so you can boost that up with Shard of Alexander and Flame Scorpion to hit for 608.<br/><br/>If you want max damage, with 99 in all 3 stats, Flame, Grant Me Strength, Golden Vow, Shard of Alexander, Flame Scorpion and Flame Tear the WA was hitting those pleb soldiers for 1k damage.<br/><br/>Really, the main issue with the WA is how easily it&apos;s interrupted. Unless you&apos;re full potato you&apos;ll be stopped by a sneeze. The only thing going for it is the duck towards the end of the animation can dodge horizontal attacks. Otherwise it&apos;s a decent tool for controlling an area and getting some health back (Especially against packs of Rats and Dogs as fire damage is especially strong against them... Just packs of those are also the most likely thing to spam you with 10 billion attacks per second to interrupt the cast)</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16717771" class="cmt-reply pull-ri